\i0\b0 \
Your soul has been somehow transported while you were sleeping to a very small dimension created entirely to punish one man.  That man had learned to control the wanderings of his soul while he slept and used it to spy on his enemies and so forth.  Eventually however, he ran into a demon who, learning of this man\'92s actions bound his soul to the fire in the fireplace (maybe the man was trying to covertly light someone\'92s home on fire).  If if goes out, not only does he die, but his soul ceases to exist and the earthly world will have no recollection he ever existed.  You are not the first to end up paying through. This dimension happens be along the rout a lot of people end up taking when they slip through space-time.  In the 10 years he\'92s been there, maybe 6-10 people have passed through.  They all leave almost immediately.  If you were to leave, you\'92d likely end up back where you left from, remembering your time there as you would a dream.\
\
The essence of the game then is to create a space that the player does not want to leave.  They will gain the ability to leave relatively quickly, but much content will still be yet to explored after that. Every time you quit and start up you\'92re a new person rolling through.  Primarily you are able to examine objects (paintings, books, letters etc) to learn more about the world, and talk the trapped man.  As he tells you stories you are able to chop some wood for him, anything to pass the time. Or you can maybe sit in the chair opposite him round the fire.\
